Media Statement Minister Pravin Gordhan has signed a deal with Coleman Andrews’ company named Bain & Co to privatise 25% of SAA. Please note BLF has asked for a Commission of Inquiry into the conduct of the same Coleman Andrews who looted SAA and bankrupted it. Pravin has instructed the Board to implement this decision. The Board meets today at the SAA Head Quarters next to  OR Tambo International airport.  BLF shall not allow this illegal conduct by Pravin Gordhan.  BLF has  written an urgent letter to the Board and to the State President asking them to halt the illegal instruction from  Gordhan.  Furthermore, BLF is calling for a picket at SAA Head Quarters this morning  and an urgent meeting  with the Board of SAA. Issued by the National Coordinating Committee, Black First Land First 29 November 2016 Contact details  Black First Land First Email:blackfirstlandfirst@gmail.com
